    <dialog class="about-dialog" id="about-dialog">
      <button
        type="button"
        class="dialog-close"
        id="about-close"
        aria-label="Close"
      >×</button>
      <div class="about-content">
        <h2>About Folio</h2>
        <p>
          Folio is a constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and
          early-reader literature. It helps you see — as you write — how your
          manuscript lands developmentally: word count vs. age-band target,
          sight-word coverage, reach words in context, phoneme inventory, and
          decodability.
        </p>
        <p>It's built for two audiences:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Picture-book authors writing toward a specific age band.</li>
          <li>
            Speech-language pathologists creating or evaluating texts with
            controlled phoneme load — click any phoneme in the sidebar to
            highlight every word containing it.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Keyboard shortcuts</h3>
        <ul class="shortcuts">
          <li><code>Cmd+B / I / U</code><span>Bold / italic / underline</span></li>
          <li><code>Cmd+Shift+X</code><span>Strikethrough</span></li>
          <li><code>Cmd+Shift+-</code><span>Soft hyphen (controls line break)</span></li>
          <li><code>Cmd+Shift+Space</code><span>Non-breaking space</span></li>
          <li><code>Cmd+F</code><span>Find &amp; replace</span></li>
          <li><code>Enter / Shift+Enter</code><span>(in Find) next / previous match</span></li>
          <li><code>← / →</code><span>(in Book view) previous / next spread</span></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Markdown shortcuts as you type</h3>
        <ul class="shortcuts">
          <li><code>**bold**</code><span>becomes <strong>bold</strong></span></li>
          <li><code>*italic*</code><span>becomes <em>italic</em></span></li>
          <li><code>~~strike~~</code><span>becomes <s>strikethrough</s></span></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Your privacy</h3>
        <p>
          Folio runs entirely in your browser. Your manuscript content never
          leaves your device — no server roundtrip, no account, no analytics
          about what you write. Your draft autosaves to this browser's local
          storage and can be cleared at any time with the Reset button.
        </p>
        <p>
          Anonymous page-view analytics are collected via
          <a href="https://plausible.io/privacy-focused-web-analytics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plausible</a> —
          cookieless, no personal data, no cross-site tracking. We see "someone
          loaded the editor page from country X," nothing more. A simpler
          paste-and-analyze surface is also available at
          <a href="/paste">/paste</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
